42. The Council recognizes progress on gender equality but stresses the need for enhanced efforts to secure the rights of women and girls, and condemns violence against women.

43. The Council welcomes the Afghan Governmentâ€™s commitment to strengthen women's participation in governance institutions and supports efforts to implement the National Action Plan for Women in Afghanistan.

44. The Council recognizes the importance of voluntary, safe, and sustainable reintegration of Afghan refugees for stability.
The Security Council:

 Calls for continued and enhanced international assistance to the country and region;

Affirms the importance of voluntary, safe, orderly return and sustainable reintegration of internally displaced persons;

Notes the need to strengthen Afghanistan's absorption capacity, with international community support, for rehabilitation and reintegration of remaining Afghan refugees and internally displaced persons;

Requests the Secretary-General to report to the Council every three months on developments in Afghanistan, including evaluation of progress against benchmarks for measuring and tracking progress in implementation of UNAMA's mandate and priorities;

Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
